6919/// printInstruction - This method is automatically generated by tablegen
6920/// from the instruction set description.
6921void MipsInstPrinter::printInstruction(const MCInst *MI, uint64_t Address, raw_ostream &O) {
6922 O << "\t";
6923
6924 auto MnemonicInfo = getMnemonic(MI);
6925
6926 O << MnemonicInfo.first;
6927
6928 uint64_t Bits = MnemonicInfo.second;
6929 assert(Bits != 0 && "Cannot print this instruction.");
6930
6931 // Fragment 0 encoded into 4 bits for 16 unique commands.
6932 switch ((Bits >> 14) & 15) {
6933 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid command number.");
6934 case 0:
6935 // DBG_VALUE, DBG_INSTR_REF, DBG_LABEL, BUNDLE, LIFETIME_START, LIFETIME_...
6936 return;
6937 break;
6938 case 1:
6939 // ABSMacro, BEQLImmMacro, BGE, BGEImmMacro, BGEL, BGELImmMacro, BGEU, BG...
6940 printOperand(MI, 0, O);
6941 break;
6942 case 2:
6943 // B_MMR6_Pseudo, B_MM_Pseudo, B16_MM, BAL, BALC, BALC_MMR6, BC, BC16_MMR...
6944 printOperand(MI, Address, 0, O);
6945 break;
6946 case 3:
6947 // CTTC1, MTTACX, MTTC0, MTTC1, MTTGPR, MTTHC1, MTTHI, MTTLO, MultRxRyRz1...
6948 printOperand(MI, 1, O);
6949 O << ", ";
6950 break;
6951 case 4:
6952 // LWM_MM, SWM_MM, LWM16_MM, LWM16_MMR6, LWM32_MM, SWM16_MM, SWM16_MMR6, ...
6953 printRegisterList(MI, 0, O);
6954 O << ", ";
6955 printMemOperand(MI, 1, O);

7595/// getRegisterName - This method is automatically generated by tblgen
7596/// from the register set description. This returns the assembler name
7597/// for the specified register.
7598const char *MipsInstPrinter::getRegisterName(unsigned RegNo) {
7599 assert(RegNo && RegNo < 442 && "Invalid register number!");
7600
7601
7602#ifdef __GNUC__
7603#pragma GCC diagnostic push
7604#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Woverlength-strings"
7605#endif
7606 static const char AsmStrs[] = {
7607 /* 0 */ "f10\0"
7608 /* 4 */ "w10\0"
7609 /* 8 */ "f20\0"
7610 /* 12 */ "DSPOutFlag20\0"
7611 /* 25 */ "w20\0"
7612 /* 29 */ "f30\0"
7613 /* 33 */ "w30\0"
7614 /* 37 */ "ac0\0"
7615 /* 41 */ "fcc0\0"

9175#ifndef NDEBUG
9176 static struct SortCheck {
9177 SortCheck(ArrayRef<PatternsForOpcode> OpToPatterns) {
9178 assert(std::is_sorted(
9179 OpToPatterns.begin(), OpToPatterns.end(),
9180 [](const PatternsForOpcode &L, const PatternsForOpcode &R) {
9181 return L.Opcode < R.Opcode;
9182 }) &&
9183 "tablegen failed to sort opcode patterns");
9184 }
9185 } sortCheckVar(OpToPatterns);
9186#endif
9187
9188 AliasMatchingData M {
9189 makeArrayRef(OpToPatterns),
9190 makeArrayRef(Patterns),
9191 makeArrayRef(Conds),
9192 StringRef(AsmStrings, array_lengthof(AsmStrings)),
9193 nullptr,
9194 };
9195 const char *AsmString = matchAliasPatterns(MI, nullptr, M);
9196 if (!AsmString) return false;
9197
9198 unsigned I = 0;
9199 while (AsmString[I] != ' ' && AsmString[I] != '\t' &&
9200 AsmString[I] != '$' && AsmString[I] != '\0')
9201 ++I;
9202 OS << '\t' << StringRef(AsmString, I);
9203 if (AsmString[I] != '\0') {
9204 if (AsmString[I] == ' ' || AsmString[I] == '\t') {
9205 OS << '\t';
9206 ++I;
9207 }
9208 do {
9209 if (AsmString[I] == '$') {
9210 ++I;
9211 if (AsmString[I] == (char)0xff) {
9212 ++I;
9213 int OpIdx = AsmString[I++] - 1;
9214 int PrintMethodIdx = AsmString[I++] - 1;
9215 printCustomAliasOperand(MI, Address, OpIdx, PrintMethodIdx, OS);
9216 } else
9217 printOperand(MI, unsigned(AsmString[I++]) - 1, OS);
9218 } else {
9219 OS << AsmString[I++];
9220 }
9221 } while (AsmString[I] != '\0');
9222 }
9223
9224 return true;
9225}
9226
9227void MipsInstPrinter::printCustomAliasOperand(
9228 const MCInst *MI, uint64_t Address, unsigned OpIdx,
9229 unsigned PrintMethodIdx,
9230 raw_ostream &OS) {
9231 switch (PrintMethodIdx) {
9232 default:
9233 llvm_unreachable("Unknown PrintMethod kind");
9234 break;
9235 case 0:
9236 printUImm<10>(MI, OpIdx, OS);
9237 break;
9238 case 1:
9239 printMemOperand(MI, OpIdx, OS);
9240 break;
9241 }
9242}
